WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:12.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.664 --> 00:32.665
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:32.732 --> 00:34.567
{\an7}- Grandpa?
Grandpa, look!

00:34.634 --> 00:36.669
{\an8}I've been practicing my fishing.

00:36.736 --> 00:37.904
{\an8}Easy...

00:37.971 --> 00:39.372
{\an8}gentle...

00:39.439 --> 00:41.107
{\an8}Ah. Okay.

00:41.174 --> 00:43.243
{\an8}Then we throw it back.
- Mm.

00:43.309 --> 00:46.112
{\an1}- Who's ready for our father/son
camping adventure?

00:46.179 --> 00:49.382
- I am! I love spending time
with my family.

00:49.449 --> 00:50.717
Mm.

00:50.784 --> 00:54.888
I'm gonna have a glass
of chocolate milk.

00:54.954 --> 00:56.956
{\an3}- Wow, the sunrise is
gorgeous today.

00:57.023 --> 00:58.158
- Mm, yeah.

00:58.224 --> 01:00.493
{\an1}- Hey, remember
our first camping trip?

01:00.560 --> 01:01.761
I still have the photo.

01:01.828 --> 01:03.563
Look how excited we were.

01:03.630 --> 01:06.533
{\an1}Huh, that's weird.
I remember you smiling.

01:06.599 --> 01:08.101
- I am smiling.

01:08.168 --> 01:10.303
- Uh, yeah, okay.

01:10.370 --> 01:12.705
You know, Dad,
I'm really glad

01:12.772 --> 01:14.707
{\an1}we get to share
this trip together.

01:14.774 --> 01:16.843
[sniffles]
- Mm.

01:16.910 --> 01:19.045
{\an1}- Gosh, and now
I've got my own kids.

01:19.112 --> 01:21.381
Time sure flies, huh?

01:21.448 --> 01:24.317
{\an3}- [slurps]

01:24.384 --> 01:27.420
{\an1}- Well, I better go load up
the supplies.

01:27.487 --> 01:29.022
- [sniffs]
- Did you say something, Dad?

01:29.088 --> 01:30.290
- No, I'm just breathing.

01:30.356 --> 01:32.425
{\an1}- Oh, I thought
I heard a--

01:32.492 --> 01:34.027
{\an1}Okay.

01:37.630 --> 01:40.567
<i>[polka music]</i>

01:40.633 --> 01:48.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:49.175 --> 01:50.477
[camera shutter clicks]

01:50.543 --> 01:52.312
{\an3}- I'm gonna capture
so many memories.

01:52.378 --> 01:55.281
- So, Dad, what are you looking
forward to most this weekend?

01:55.348 --> 01:58.084
- Ah, you know, the quiet.

01:58.151 --> 02:00.053
- Uh-huh, yeah, sure.
That sounds great.

02:00.119 --> 02:03.289
Oh, hey, look.
Look at all of our friends here.

02:03.356 --> 02:05.091
[indistinct chatter
and laughter]

02:05.158 --> 02:07.494
- Hey,
the Beaks boys are here.

02:07.560 --> 02:10.697
- Oh-ho-ho, man,
now it's a party.

02:10.763 --> 02:12.031
[camera shutter clicks]

02:12.098 --> 02:13.900
- Who are these people?
- Wow!

02:13.967 --> 02:16.102
{\an3}Everyone is
on a father/son retreat.

02:16.169 --> 02:19.172
- Yep, me and my dad are
so pumped for this.

02:19.239 --> 02:21.241
We love camping together.

02:21.307 --> 02:23.576
- Um, that's a statue.

02:23.643 --> 02:24.878
- It's a long story.

02:24.944 --> 02:26.145
- Oh, oh, I have an idea.

02:26.212 --> 02:28.448
Why don't we all camp together?

02:28.515 --> 02:30.016
Uh, here, go mingle.

02:30.083 --> 02:31.985
- Dad, what's going on?

02:32.051 --> 02:34.587
{\an1}I thought this was
a family trip.

02:34.654 --> 02:35.955
- I have a confession.

02:36.022 --> 02:38.391
{\an3}This weekend isn't
just about us camping.

02:38.458 --> 02:41.761
{\an3}I want my dad to open up
about his feelings.

02:41.828 --> 02:44.397
{\an1}- You mean like how we're open
about our feelings

02:44.464 --> 02:46.399
with each other?
- Yes, exactly.

02:46.466 --> 02:48.535
{\an1}- Like how I can tell you
whenever I feel--

02:48.601 --> 02:49.536
- Not now, son.

02:49.602 --> 02:50.737
He's my dad,

02:50.803 --> 02:52.772
but I don't really know
much about him.

02:52.839 --> 02:54.874
Like, what's
his favorite ice cream flavor?

02:54.941 --> 02:57.210
Is it chocolate or pistachio?

02:57.277 --> 02:59.012
{\an3}The books I've read said
it's easier to open up

02:59.078 --> 03:00.346
in a group setting.

03:00.413 --> 03:03.016
{\an1}- Wow, if a book said it,
then it must be true.

03:03.082 --> 03:04.984
- I'm gonna need your help.
- Yeah.

03:05.051 --> 03:08.054
Let's make Grandpa cry.

03:08.121 --> 03:09.989
{\an1}- Let's go around
and just share something

03:10.056 --> 03:11.891
we've never told anyone before.

03:11.958 --> 03:14.494
{\an3}- I thought we were just
gonna roast some marshmallows.

03:14.561 --> 03:16.629
{\an1}- Dad, don't worry.
We're just having some guy talk.

03:16.696 --> 03:17.830
Here, I'll start.

03:17.897 --> 03:20.066
{\an1}The new baby keeps
Miriam and I up all night

03:20.133 --> 03:22.235
with her crying,
and sometimes...

03:22.302 --> 03:24.904
{\an1}that makes me feel like
a real grouch.

03:24.971 --> 03:27.640
{\an1}- Sometimes
I like to turn down my beats

03:27.707 --> 03:29.342
and just listen to the rain.

03:29.409 --> 03:31.010
It makes me feel wistful.

03:31.077 --> 03:32.245
- Bro, me too!

03:32.312 --> 03:34.647
{\an1}- Whoa, I thought
I was the only one.

03:34.714 --> 03:35.915
- That's good.

03:35.982 --> 03:38.284
{\an3}- Sometimes
I think I'm always preparing

03:38.351 --> 03:39.953
for future disasters,

03:40.019 --> 03:41.821
{\an3}but I'm never enjoying
the present.

03:41.888 --> 03:44.624
{\an1}- Well, I like
using my wife's razor to shave.

03:44.691 --> 03:47.427
{\an1}It's lighter,
and it makes me feel nice.

03:47.493 --> 03:50.096
{\an3}- This is--this is all
very personal.

03:50.163 --> 03:51.497
- Guys, let's all get up

03:51.564 --> 03:53.232
and form a ring of compassion
around Mitch.

03:53.299 --> 03:54.701
{\an1}- Yeah, yeah, we should come on
and go help him out.

03:54.767 --> 03:56.135
- Yeah, love you, Dad.
Yeah, you're amazing.

03:56.202 --> 03:57.670
- What about you, Dad?

03:57.737 --> 03:59.806
Do you have anything
to share...

03:59.872 --> 04:01.507
specifically with me...

04:01.574 --> 04:03.343
your son?

04:03.409 --> 04:04.877
- Uh...
[clears throat]

04:04.944 --> 04:06.312
I feel...

04:06.379 --> 04:08.581
like I got to use
the bathroom.

04:11.017 --> 04:13.953
{\an1}[snoring]

04:14.020 --> 04:16.755
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

04:16.822 --> 04:18.156
- Dad?
- Yeah?

04:18.224 --> 04:19.759
- What you thinking about?

04:19.826 --> 04:20.994
- Mm, nothing.

04:21.060 --> 04:23.196
{\an3}- Come on.
You can't fool me.

04:23.262 --> 04:25.465
- [sighs]
I don't think my plan

04:25.531 --> 04:27.300
to have Grandpa open up
is gonna work.

04:27.367 --> 04:28.801
{\an3}- You've got
the whole weekend.

04:28.868 --> 04:31.871
{\an3}I know you can do it.
I believe in you.

04:31.938 --> 04:33.673
- Thanks, son.

04:33.740 --> 04:35.708
{\an3}Tomorrow
I'm gonna double down

04:35.775 --> 04:38.778
{\an3}and have an honest, open moment
with my father.

04:38.845 --> 04:41.147
- [snoring]

04:41.214 --> 04:42.749
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:42.815 --> 04:45.418
- Okay, Dad, I want you
to cross your arms

04:45.485 --> 04:48.388
and let yourself fall back
so Harvey and I can catch you.

04:48.454 --> 04:51.124
- Uh, this doesn't feel right.

04:51.190 --> 04:53.426
Better.
- Mm, no, but the--

04:53.493 --> 04:55.628
{\an3}but the point
of the trust exercise is--

04:55.695 --> 04:58.031
- Mm...

04:58.097 --> 04:59.799
[grunts]
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

04:59.866 --> 05:01.634
That's enough of that.

05:01.701 --> 05:03.803
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:03.870 --> 05:05.471
- I got you, Dad.

05:07.273 --> 05:08.841
- This one's called
the Trust Cage.

05:08.908 --> 05:11.711
While our hands are linked,
we each share something

05:11.778 --> 05:13.713
and untangle ourselves
to get free.

05:13.780 --> 05:16.215
- [ grumbles]
It's really hot in here.

05:16.282 --> 05:18.251
You know, this is
how bees kill each other.

05:18.317 --> 05:19.719
- No cheating, Grandpa.

05:19.786 --> 05:21.921
You have to communicate
to get out.

05:21.988 --> 05:25.291
{\an3}- Yo, sorry, everybody,
but I'm not wearing deodorant.

05:25.358 --> 05:27.093
{\an8}- Tell me something.
What are you feeling?

05:27.160 --> 05:30.830
{\an8}The longer you stay silent,
the longer we stay tangled.

05:30.897 --> 05:33.833
- [grunting]

05:33.900 --> 05:38.404
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:38.471 --> 05:40.339
{\an1}There.

05:42.208 --> 05:43.710
[both screaming]

05:43.776 --> 05:46.579
both:
I've got emotions!

05:46.646 --> 05:49.849
- Okay, Dad, your turn
to do the yelling sprint.

05:49.916 --> 05:51.451
- Whoo.

05:51.517 --> 05:53.720
- Harvey and I are waiting
to hug you at the finish line.

05:53.786 --> 05:56.556
- [grunts]
- I got you, Grandpa.

05:56.622 --> 05:59.659
- Uh, I think I'm gonna
go back to camp.

05:59.726 --> 06:01.461
{\an3}- Whee!

06:05.131 --> 06:06.399
- Time to sit.

06:06.466 --> 06:07.934
- Are you having fun, Grandpa?

06:08.000 --> 06:10.436
{\an3}Isn't being emotionally honest
the best?

06:10.503 --> 06:13.072
{\an1}- This is
a very strange camping trip.

06:13.139 --> 06:14.540
- "Strange"?

06:14.607 --> 06:17.477
{\an3}I don't think Dad
wants you to feel strange.

06:17.543 --> 06:19.545
He just wants to bond with you.

06:19.612 --> 06:21.948
{\an1}- Bond?
Why didn't he say so?

06:22.014 --> 06:23.750
I know how to do that.

06:23.816 --> 06:26.319
<i>[soft music]</i>

06:26.385 --> 06:27.687
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:27.754 --> 06:30.623
- So, um, Dad,
what do you call this exercise?

06:30.690 --> 06:32.058
{\an3}- Fishing.

06:32.125 --> 06:35.695
{\an3}- I get it--the fish are like
traumatic memories,

06:35.762 --> 06:37.663
{\an3}and the poles
represent healing.

06:37.730 --> 06:41.000
- The water is obviously
a window and a mirror.

06:41.067 --> 06:45.271
- I think we're forgetting
to use "I feel" statements.

06:45.338 --> 06:48.641
{\an1}You should say,
"I feel that the water is--"

06:48.708 --> 06:52.779
- Okay, I'm experiencing a lot
of micro-aggression right now.

06:52.845 --> 06:55.515
- Dad, this is great,
but there's not much room

06:55.581 --> 06:57.817
for us to connect
if we just sit in silence.

06:57.884 --> 07:01.087
- I think all this talking
is scaring away the fish.

07:01.154 --> 07:02.555
{\an1}- Mm.

07:02.622 --> 07:04.490
Maybe this was a mistake.

07:04.557 --> 07:05.925
You guys have fun fishing.

07:05.992 --> 07:07.727
I'm--I'm just gonna go.

07:07.794 --> 07:09.495
- Grandpa...

07:09.562 --> 07:11.364
- Uh, um, son, wait.

07:11.430 --> 07:14.033
{\an3}Listen, this is,
uh, very new to me.

07:14.100 --> 07:17.503
{\an3}I-I-I don't--I don't know
what you want from me,

07:17.570 --> 07:19.172
but I want to try.

07:19.238 --> 07:21.107
- You--you mean it?

07:21.174 --> 07:22.975
{\an3}- Mm-hmm.

07:23.042 --> 07:25.812
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:25.878 --> 07:28.281
- I'm gonna guide you
on a trust walk.

07:28.347 --> 07:29.916
{\an3}- Do I have to wear
a blindfold?

07:29.982 --> 07:32.451
{\an1}- Yes, you've got to trust me
to give you directions

07:32.518 --> 07:34.086
to get through this.

07:34.153 --> 07:38.558
{\an1}When we emerge, we'll have a
stronger bond than ever before.

07:38.624 --> 07:40.526
Just keep going straight.
- Okay.

07:40.593 --> 07:42.428
- Slight left.
- All right.

07:42.495 --> 07:44.230
{\an1}- Do you feel yourself
being more open yet?

07:44.297 --> 07:47.667
- I just feel like I can't see.
- We'll get there together, Dad.

07:47.733 --> 07:50.169
I really appreciate
you giving this a try.

07:50.236 --> 07:52.605
Ooh, what's that?

07:52.672 --> 07:54.507
Well, hello, there.

07:54.574 --> 07:56.642
Oh, is that a picture of me?

07:56.709 --> 07:59.111
Oh, that's really something.

07:59.178 --> 08:01.247
It looks just--Dad?

08:01.314 --> 08:03.049
Dad?

08:03.115 --> 08:04.383
- Oh, they're back already.

08:04.450 --> 08:05.618
[camera shutter clicks]
- This is terrible!

08:05.685 --> 08:07.353
- What happened?
- I lost Grandpa!

08:07.420 --> 08:09.155
- You did what?
- [screams]

08:09.222 --> 08:11.290
- [screams]

08:11.357 --> 08:13.626
Aah, aah, aah!
- Aah, this is my fault!

08:13.693 --> 08:15.094
- Where did you see him last?

08:15.161 --> 08:17.396
{\an3}- I think we were by
the sharp sticks and quicksand.

08:17.463 --> 08:19.065
- Oh, no, look!

08:19.131 --> 08:20.800
Grandpa!
- Grandpa?

08:20.867 --> 08:22.335
I'm only 29!

08:22.401 --> 08:23.669
{\an3}- Have you seen
an old man around?

08:23.736 --> 08:25.738
{\an1}- He's stout,
and he doesn't like hugs.

08:25.805 --> 08:28.107
- Oh, yeah, he went that way.

08:28.174 --> 08:29.609
<i>[lilting tense music]</i>

08:29.675 --> 08:30.810
{\an1}- [gasps]
Grandpa.

08:30.877 --> 08:32.578
{\an3}- Harvey, wait here.
I'll get him.

08:32.645 --> 08:36.048
- Son, a-aren't you supposed
to be guiding me?

08:36.115 --> 08:38.417
{\an3}What's with
the silent treatment?

08:38.484 --> 08:41.419
{\an3}Oh, this is how you must feel
when you're around me.

08:41.486 --> 08:43.522
Okay, point taken.

08:43.589 --> 08:45.458
Doesn't feel good.

08:45.524 --> 08:46.859
Well, right now

08:46.926 --> 08:49.595
{\an3}I'm wishing I had
some accordion music.

08:49.662 --> 08:51.597
I find it soothing.

08:51.664 --> 08:54.467
{\an1}- What?
I never knew that.

08:54.533 --> 08:55.735
- You haven't made a peep,

08:55.801 --> 08:58.237
{\an3}so I guess you want me
to keep going.

08:58.304 --> 09:00.406
Let me see, um, well,

09:00.473 --> 09:02.608
{\an3}I have a strong stance
on pretzels.

09:02.675 --> 09:04.610
- Oh, Grandpa, we found you!

09:04.677 --> 09:07.013
{\an3}- [whispering] Harvey, wait.
Let's just go with it.

09:07.079 --> 09:10.750
{\an3}The silence, it's making Dad
open up for the first time ever.

09:10.816 --> 09:12.752
- But he could get hurt.
- I don't want to mess this up.

09:12.818 --> 09:14.186
If we don't make any sounds,

09:14.253 --> 09:16.756
{\an3}then Dad will feel safe
to just keep sharing.

09:16.822 --> 09:19.959
{\an1}- No, seriously, he's gonna
get hurt right now. Look!

09:20.026 --> 09:22.662
- In my book, pretzel chips
are not actually pretzels.

09:22.728 --> 09:24.030
[all chomping and growling]

09:24.096 --> 09:26.732
{\an3}- [gasps]
I'm gonna save him very quietly.

09:26.799 --> 09:29.835
{\an3}- Well, I'm not
a fan of movies nowadays.

09:29.902 --> 09:32.271
{\an1}I didn't care for
the "Explosion World" sequel.

09:32.338 --> 09:33.439
I'll say it.

09:33.506 --> 09:35.641
{\an1}I mean, sure,
the set pieces were fun,

09:35.708 --> 09:37.710
{\an1}but it's like everything
in the first movie

09:37.777 --> 09:40.379
never even happened.
- [gasps]

09:40.446 --> 09:42.581
- They just threw away
all the character development.

09:42.648 --> 09:44.183
It was a real shame.

09:44.250 --> 09:46.953
And I got into baking
because it's like chemistry.

09:47.019 --> 09:49.288
And that's why I don't keep
those cookies in the house.

09:49.355 --> 09:51.023
I can't.
I'll eat them all.

09:51.090 --> 09:52.158
- [gurgling]

09:52.224 --> 09:54.193
- I guess my most favorite smell

09:54.260 --> 09:55.761
is laundry detergent.

09:55.828 --> 09:57.330
- [gasps]
Mm...

09:57.396 --> 10:00.333
[grunts]

10:00.399 --> 10:03.336
[straining]

10:03.402 --> 10:06.305
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

10:06.372 --> 10:07.673
- Son, I--

10:07.740 --> 10:09.775
You know,
I know we're very different

10:09.842 --> 10:11.844
and sometimes I can be tough,

10:11.911 --> 10:14.880
{\an8}but, um, I-I just want to say,
I'm proud of you.

10:14.947 --> 10:16.749
{\an8}You're not
the physically strong type,

10:16.816 --> 10:19.652
{\an8}but you carry
a lot of emotional weight.

10:19.719 --> 10:22.388
{\an8}You're a good father,
and you're a good son.

10:22.455 --> 10:24.023
- [squeaks]

10:24.090 --> 10:26.726
- All right,
um, enough of that.

10:26.792 --> 10:30.363
So let's, uh, finish
this trust walk.

10:30.429 --> 10:31.697
<i>[soft music]</i>

10:31.764 --> 10:35.167
- [panting]
We made it.

10:35.234 --> 10:36.302
{\an3}- Good.

10:36.369 --> 10:38.437
Ah, what a nice sunset.

10:38.504 --> 10:40.506
- Dad, Grandpa.
- Harvey.

10:40.573 --> 10:42.008
- Did you know
about the stair lift

10:42.074 --> 10:44.010
that goes all the way
up the mountain?

10:44.076 --> 10:46.112
{\an3}- Well, that--that went
pretty smoothly.

10:46.178 --> 10:48.447
{\an1}- Actually,
there were several close calls.

10:48.514 --> 10:50.449
{\an3}- I told you
you'd be save with me.

10:50.516 --> 10:51.784
{\an1}- [muffled]
He wasn't, though.

10:51.851 --> 10:54.320
{\an8}- I really feel like
I get you now, Dad.

10:54.387 --> 10:55.788
- Mm-hmm.

10:55.855 --> 10:58.457
- Well, we better head back.

10:58.524 --> 11:01.727
{\an3}- We could, uh, take
a picture.

11:01.794 --> 11:04.196
- Really?
Sure!

11:04.263 --> 11:06.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:06.665 --> 11:09.602
[camera shutter clicking]

11:09.668 --> 11:14.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:16.709 --> 11:17.643
<i>[lilting music]</i>

11:17.710 --> 11:19.979
- [laughs]

11:20.046 --> 11:23.149
- You'll never catch us,
Sheriff Beaks.

11:23.215 --> 11:25.551
- You evil twins have done
messed things up

11:25.618 --> 11:27.153
for the last time.

11:27.219 --> 11:29.555
[all laughing]

11:29.622 --> 11:31.223
[both grunt]
- [laughs]

11:31.290 --> 11:32.925
- [grunts]

11:32.992 --> 11:34.493
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

11:34.560 --> 11:35.861
{\an3}- You okay?

11:35.928 --> 11:38.230
- Yeah, my head broke my fall.

11:38.297 --> 11:41.067
Hey, it's kind of neat
down here.

11:41.133 --> 11:41.967
[gasps]

11:42.034 --> 11:45.204
Guys, you got to see this!

11:45.271 --> 11:47.273
both: Whoa!

11:47.339 --> 11:50.242
- What do you think's inside?
- Pirate booty!

11:50.309 --> 11:52.445
- What if it's
just another bag

11:52.511 --> 11:56.015
and then we open that bag
and find another bag,

11:56.082 --> 11:58.250
then another, then another,

11:58.317 --> 11:59.885
until they get so small

11:59.952 --> 12:01.887
that the last tiny bag just has

12:01.954 --> 12:03.722
a little tiny note in it?

12:03.789 --> 12:06.225
- What's the note say?
- Um...

12:06.292 --> 12:07.560
"Always be yourself."

12:07.626 --> 12:08.727
{\an1}- I will.

12:08.794 --> 12:10.763
{\an3}- Come on,
open it already.

12:10.830 --> 12:12.198
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:12.264 --> 12:14.567
all: Whoa.

12:14.633 --> 12:22.775
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:26.579 --> 12:28.948
- They look like weird plants.

12:29.014 --> 12:30.749
Who do you think
these belong to?

12:30.816 --> 12:33.352
- Who cares?
They're ours now.

12:33.419 --> 12:34.653
[growls]

12:34.720 --> 12:36.822
Ew, what even are these things?

12:36.889 --> 12:40.459
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

12:40.526 --> 12:43.462
all: Whoa.

12:43.529 --> 12:45.764
Whoa.

12:45.831 --> 12:47.233
- That was so cool!
- That was so amazing!

12:47.299 --> 12:48.934
- That was the best thing
I've ever seen in my life.

12:49.001 --> 12:50.636
- I want to try one.

12:50.703 --> 12:52.071
Ha ha ha.

12:52.138 --> 12:53.305
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:53.372 --> 12:55.774
- Oh, jeez.
- Dude, are you all right?

12:55.841 --> 12:58.711
- Don't worry, guys.
I'm fine.

12:58.777 --> 13:00.279
Oh.

13:00.346 --> 13:02.281
{\an1}- Oh, my gosh,
he's dismembered.

13:02.348 --> 13:04.750
{\an1}I think--I think
I'm gonna be sick.

13:04.817 --> 13:07.286
- Nah, it's just hair.
See?

13:09.121 --> 13:10.389
[spits]

13:10.456 --> 13:12.491
There.

13:12.558 --> 13:14.627
- Oh, no.

13:14.693 --> 13:18.464
{\an3}- Okay, what if we set them
all off at the same time?

13:18.531 --> 13:19.965
- Ooh, that could be cool.

13:20.032 --> 13:22.635
- No!
Get away from those!

13:22.701 --> 13:24.170
- Hey.
- Children...

13:24.236 --> 13:26.772
oh, you shouldn't
be messing with those things.

13:26.839 --> 13:29.575
They're the pods
of the Barkqoiuse plant,

13:29.642 --> 13:31.577
and they're evil incarnate!

13:31.644 --> 13:33.646
Anyone who plays with them

13:33.712 --> 13:35.948
lives to regret it.

13:36.015 --> 13:38.450
- Jeremy, you're kind of
freaking me out.

13:38.517 --> 13:42.388
{\an1}- Come on.
These don't seem so dangerous.

13:42.454 --> 13:44.757
- Oh, you think so, huh?

13:44.823 --> 13:46.659
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:46.725 --> 13:48.460
- Ew, sick.
- Oh, my goodness.

13:48.527 --> 13:49.728
- You look silly.

13:49.795 --> 13:51.397
- Yeah, they seem fun
to play with.

13:51.463 --> 13:55.501
They're so--so dangerous
and--and alluring, you know?

13:55.568 --> 13:57.836
Just one look at them,

13:57.903 --> 13:59.872
and you can--

13:59.939 --> 14:01.173
Oh, what's that?

14:01.240 --> 14:03.509
You want me to set you off?

14:03.576 --> 14:06.445
Well, you know, maybe I'll--
I'll just set one off--

14:06.512 --> 14:09.949
Aah, aah! Get this evil thing
away from me!

14:10.015 --> 14:11.884
{\an8}both: Aah!
[whistling]

14:15.688 --> 14:18.357
- Man, I think Jeremy's right.

14:18.424 --> 14:19.925
That bag is bad news.

14:19.992 --> 14:21.427
{\an3}We should probably
get rid of it.

14:21.493 --> 14:22.962
- Don't worry.
I'm already on it.

14:23.028 --> 14:24.964
- No, evil like this

14:25.030 --> 14:27.499
can't be vanquished
with a measly hammer.

14:27.566 --> 14:29.401
No, there's only one place

14:29.468 --> 14:32.538
where those pods
can be safely destroyed.

14:32.605 --> 14:35.307
<i>You'll go</i>
<i>through Deathbark Woods,</i>

14:35.374 --> 14:37.876
<i>trek through Swampbark Marsh,</i>

14:37.943 --> 14:40.246
<i>hike along</i>
<i>the Steepbark Trail,</i>

14:40.312 --> 14:42.114
and then I think
you take a left or...

14:42.181 --> 14:44.149
I don't know.
Maybe it's a right.

14:44.216 --> 14:46.085
<i>Anyhoo, you get</i>
<i>to the Bigbark Mountains,</i>

14:46.151 --> 14:49.888
<i>and within those mountains</i>
<i>is a bottomless pit,</i>

14:49.955 --> 14:52.858
<i>and that is where</i>
<i>you must throw the bag.</i>

14:52.925 --> 14:55.060
- Whoa.

14:55.127 --> 14:56.862
Great.
Let's get moving, then.

14:56.929 --> 14:59.398
{\an1}- Me?
No, no, no, I can't.

14:59.465 --> 15:00.599
Oh-ho, maybe I can...

15:00.666 --> 15:02.534
{\an1}No! I got to go take
a cold shower!

15:02.601 --> 15:04.036
[screaming]

15:04.103 --> 15:07.039
- Well, then, it's up to us.

15:07.106 --> 15:08.941
♪ Doop doop,
going on a journey ♪

15:09.008 --> 15:10.909
♪ Doop doop,
got a lot of walkin' ♪

15:10.976 --> 15:12.011
♪ Doop doop,
doobie-doobie-doobie-doobie... ♪

15:12.077 --> 15:13.545
- Psst.
Psst.

15:13.612 --> 15:15.381
- Huh?
Who said that?

15:15.447 --> 15:17.950
{\an3}- Oh, hey, there,
little gremlin boy.

15:18.017 --> 15:19.118
- Did you just talk?

15:19.184 --> 15:21.787
{\an1}Harvey, I think this bag
is a witch.

15:21.854 --> 15:23.656
A wi--
- I ain't no witch.

15:23.722 --> 15:25.524
I'm in your head.
- Wow.

15:25.591 --> 15:27.660
{\an1}People always say
there's nothing in my head.

15:27.726 --> 15:29.295
- Hey, you look like a fun guy.

15:29.361 --> 15:31.664
{\an3}Tell me, slick,
you like to party?

15:31.730 --> 15:32.965
- I like birthday parties.

15:33.032 --> 15:35.801
- How about a plant pod party?

15:35.868 --> 15:37.703
{\an1}- Oh.

15:37.770 --> 15:41.307
- Hey, Foo, how many of these
things you think I can whack?

15:41.373 --> 15:42.474
Foo?

15:42.541 --> 15:44.443
- Ha ha ha ha.

15:44.510 --> 15:45.678
Oh.

15:45.744 --> 15:48.547
{\an3}- Maybe I better
hold the bag for a while.

15:48.614 --> 15:49.915
- Bye, talking bag.

15:49.982 --> 15:51.784
- Harvey,
do we really got to walk

15:51.850 --> 15:53.385
all the way to the mountains?

15:53.452 --> 15:56.522
What do you say we just go dump
this thing in a river somewhere.

15:56.588 --> 15:58.757
{\an3}- Fee, you know
we can't do that.

15:58.824 --> 16:02.695
{\an3}W-what if a baby finds it
and blows his little head off?

16:02.761 --> 16:04.296
Oh, that's awful--

16:04.363 --> 16:06.498
{\an3}little headless babies
everywhere.

16:06.565 --> 16:09.668
{\an3}We have to dispose
of this thing properly.

16:09.735 --> 16:12.671
<i>[funky upbeat music]</i>

16:12.738 --> 16:14.306
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:14.373 --> 16:17.142
{\an1}- Psst, well,
hey, there, little lady.

16:17.209 --> 16:19.311
- Buddy, don't try anything.

16:19.378 --> 16:22.414
{\an3}I got voices in my head telling
me what to do all the time.

16:22.481 --> 16:24.316
{\an3}- Cause some trouble.
Start a fire.

16:24.383 --> 16:26.352
- Shoo, I'm busy.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

16:26.418 --> 16:27.786
- [humming]

16:27.853 --> 16:29.855
Hey, anyone want
a nutritious snack?

16:29.922 --> 16:31.190
[gasps]

16:31.256 --> 16:33.058
- I think I have a problem.

16:33.125 --> 16:36.462
- No, you got to resist
the bag's power, Fee.

16:36.528 --> 16:38.864
Resist it...

16:38.931 --> 16:39.932
<i>[ominous music]</i>

16:39.998 --> 16:42.701
Ha ha ha.

16:42.768 --> 16:45.537
{\an3}- We've got to be
more careful, guys.

16:45.604 --> 16:47.072
This bag is powerful.

16:47.139 --> 16:48.607
{\an1}- You're right.
I'm sorry.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.109
You got to carry it, Harvey.

16:50.175 --> 16:51.510
- You're strong of will.

16:51.577 --> 16:54.380
- Really?
Okay, I'll do it...

16:54.446 --> 16:56.548
for the babies.

16:56.615 --> 16:57.916
<i>[lilting music]</i>

16:57.983 --> 16:59.218
♪ Doop doop,
resisting temptation ♪

16:59.284 --> 17:01.053
♪ Doop doop,
saving the babies ♪

17:01.120 --> 17:03.355
{\an1}- Well, now,
that's some nice singing.

17:03.422 --> 17:06.759
- Thank you, Mr. Bag.
- I bet you're responsible too.

17:06.825 --> 17:08.594
- Oh, very much so.

17:08.660 --> 17:10.128
I always take my vitamins,

17:10.194 --> 17:13.165
{\an3}and you'll never
see these teeth unbrushed.

17:13.232 --> 17:15.768
{\an1}- You're much more responsible
than the others.

17:15.834 --> 17:16.769
- [humming]
- Heck...

17:16.835 --> 17:18.904
Foo blew off his dang curl.

17:18.971 --> 17:21.339
- I'd never do that.
- Exactly.

17:21.406 --> 17:24.041
So why not have a little fun?

17:24.108 --> 17:27.579
- Yeah, fun is good.

17:27.646 --> 17:28.947
[gasps]

17:29.014 --> 17:30.716
- Harvey, you okay?

17:30.783 --> 17:32.951
- Oh, uh, totally.

17:33.018 --> 17:35.554
{\an1}The bag's just getting
kind of heavy.

17:35.621 --> 17:39.158
{\an1}Could you, like,
sing a song or something?

17:39.224 --> 17:41.226
Just to keep me focused.

17:41.293 --> 17:44.763
<i>- ♪ Off on a journey,</i>
<i>treacherous and long ♪</i>

17:44.830 --> 17:47.800
♪ A perfect place
for a creepy folk song ♪

17:47.866 --> 17:51.136
- ♪ I played with a plant,
and it blew off my curl ♪

17:51.203 --> 17:54.873
♪ Those plant pods are dangerous
but really fun ♪

17:54.940 --> 17:56.442
Oh, rhyming's hard.

17:56.508 --> 17:59.645
all:
♪ Hi-ho, off we go ♪

17:59.711 --> 18:03.015
♪ Three best friends
on an epic quest ♪

18:03.081 --> 18:06.285
both:
♪ Harvey he's our hero ♪

18:06.351 --> 18:09.588
all: ♪ Together we march
into the west ♪

18:09.655 --> 18:11.323
{\an3}- No, Foo, we want
to go this way.

18:11.390 --> 18:14.560
- ♪ A bag of burden,
too heavy for a friend ♪

18:14.626 --> 18:17.796
♪ So I must carry it
to the end ♪

18:17.863 --> 18:21.233
♪ But I am careful,
I even cover my coughs ♪

18:21.300 --> 18:24.837
♪ So what's the harm
in setting one off? ♪

18:24.903 --> 18:27.506
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:27.573 --> 18:30.843
[laughs evilly]

18:30.909 --> 18:31.877
{\an3}- Harvey!

18:31.944 --> 18:34.780
<i>[ominous music]</i>

18:34.847 --> 18:36.815
- ♪ Washing my body ♪

18:36.882 --> 18:39.618
[pod whistles and explodes]

18:39.685 --> 18:41.887
So pretty...

18:41.954 --> 18:44.022
No, no, I-I can't.

18:44.089 --> 18:47.392
I-I must stay strong...

18:47.459 --> 18:48.393
[grunts]

18:48.460 --> 18:51.129
I'm coming for you, baby!

18:51.196 --> 18:53.465
[laughs maniacally]

18:53.532 --> 18:54.933
[explosions]

18:55.000 --> 18:56.068
- What the heck, man?

18:56.134 --> 18:57.803
{\an1}- I-I don't know.
I--

18:57.870 --> 19:00.072
{\an3}- You were supposed
to be strong of will.

19:00.138 --> 19:02.007
[grunting]

19:02.074 --> 19:03.475
This bag is evil!

19:03.542 --> 19:05.944
- [crying]
I-I'm so sorry, guys.

19:06.011 --> 19:07.446
I don't know what came over me.

19:07.513 --> 19:11.550
I was weak!
I was weak!

19:11.617 --> 19:14.086
- Guys, we can't give up now.
- Shh.

19:14.152 --> 19:15.821
- We're almost there.

19:15.888 --> 19:16.889
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:16.955 --> 19:18.390
As individuals, we're weak,

19:18.457 --> 19:20.893
but as a group,
we're less weak.

19:20.959 --> 19:23.896
The only way we can destroy
this stupid thing

19:23.962 --> 19:25.764
is by carrying it together.

19:25.831 --> 19:27.299
{\an3}- Or not.

19:27.366 --> 19:30.502
all: ♪ Tired and weary
and starting to drag ♪

19:30.569 --> 19:32.170
- ♪ You guys could
just party-- ♪

19:32.237 --> 19:33.839
- ♪ Shut up, you dumb bag ♪

19:33.906 --> 19:36.041
all: ♪ Journey's long,
but stay strong ♪

19:36.108 --> 19:37.643
- ♪ Look, finish line ♪

19:37.709 --> 19:39.511
all:
♪ Three brave travelers ♪

19:39.578 --> 19:41.713
♪ We'll be just fine ♪

19:41.780 --> 19:43.015
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:43.081 --> 19:45.551
- ♪ You ain't going nowhere ♪

19:45.617 --> 19:50.455
♪ The plant pods are mine! ♪

19:50.522 --> 19:52.858
<i>[eerie music]</i>
- [grunts]

19:52.925 --> 19:54.259
- Ah, we made it.

19:54.326 --> 19:56.962
I've never seen anything
so beautiful.

19:57.029 --> 19:59.898
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:59.965 --> 20:02.200
It was a rough journey,
but we looked out for each other

20:02.267 --> 20:03.835
because friends don't--

20:03.902 --> 20:06.305
{\an1}- Yeah, yeah, yeah. Let's just
get rid of this dang thing.

20:06.371 --> 20:09.708
- Okay. Let's do it
on the count of three.

20:09.775 --> 20:11.743
- One...
- Two...

20:11.810 --> 20:12.844
- Three.

20:12.911 --> 20:15.380
- Okay, it's done.

20:17.316 --> 20:18.984
Harvey?
What are you doing?

20:19.051 --> 20:21.520
- But maybe
we shouldn't destroy the bag.

20:21.587 --> 20:23.722
I mean, what's the bag
ever done to us?

20:23.789 --> 20:24.890
- [panting]

20:24.957 --> 20:26.692
{\an1}[yells]

20:26.758 --> 20:27.726
[grunts]

20:27.793 --> 20:28.827
{\an3}- [grunts]

20:28.894 --> 20:31.163
- [grunting]

20:31.229 --> 20:33.298
- [grunting]

20:33.365 --> 20:35.300
[both straining]
- Give me! Give it to me!

20:35.367 --> 20:36.368
- No, no, it's mine.
- Jeremy!

20:36.435 --> 20:37.769
{\an1}- The bag is mine!
Give it to me!

20:37.836 --> 20:39.371
{\an1}- They're perfectly matched
in strength.

20:39.438 --> 20:41.039
We have to help him.

20:41.106 --> 20:42.307
[both shouting]
- [straining]

20:42.374 --> 20:44.309
{\an1}- Harvey,
get the bag to the pit.

20:44.376 --> 20:46.178
- But I-I--

20:46.244 --> 20:49.615
- Give me the bag!
I need it!

20:49.681 --> 20:50.882
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:50.949 --> 20:52.217
- Oh, my gosh.

20:52.284 --> 20:54.386
This bag changes people,

20:54.453 --> 20:56.688
and it started to change me.

20:56.755 --> 20:58.991
I don't want to end up
like Jeremy.

20:59.057 --> 21:00.993
- Aw, don't worry about him.

21:01.059 --> 21:02.594
Let's have a pod party!

21:02.661 --> 21:05.831
- No, I'm tired of you
messing with me and my friends.

21:05.897 --> 21:09.134
{\an1}- Hey, hey, hey, come on, man.
I thought you were cool.

21:09.201 --> 21:10.135
[both straining]

21:10.202 --> 21:11.837
- [shouting]

21:11.903 --> 21:15.974
{\an1}- You'll never feel
the thrill of these pods again.

21:16.041 --> 21:17.943
- That's enough out of you.

21:18.010 --> 21:20.212
Time to go to hole.

21:20.278 --> 21:21.246
- Aw, man.

21:21.313 --> 21:24.983
- No!

21:26.785 --> 21:28.487
- [sighs]

21:28.553 --> 21:31.523
- Is it really over?
- I think so.

21:31.590 --> 21:34.259
No one will ever have
to deal with those pods ever--

21:34.326 --> 21:37.262
[pods whistling and exploding]

21:37.329 --> 21:40.265
<i>[wondrous music]</i>

21:40.332 --> 21:48.473
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:52.477 --> 21:55.714
{\an3}- Wow.
Now, that was beautiful.

21:55.781 --> 21:58.050
- It sure was.

21:58.116 --> 22:00.752
Did anyone bring bandages?
